# EFU Development Session
## 2026-03-10

### Topic
EFU 600-series – Foundational layer development

---

## Starting Point

The discussion began from an ontological question regarding the position of humans in the biosphere, the introduction of synthetic materials, and the EFU reversibility thesis.

This led to the recognition that the **600-series lacked a theoretical and operational base layer**. Modules such as **600.52 (PFAS)** were standing without a systemic foundation.

---

## Modules Completed

### 600.0 – SBE Article 0
System Boundary Event definition and criteria.

### 600.2 – Molecular System Boundary Events
Classification and criteria for molecular boundary violations.

### 600.3 – Biogeochemical Cycle Disruptions
Carbon, nitrogen, phosphorus, water and oxygen cycle disturbances.

### 600.4 – Ecosystem Resilience Thresholds
Tipping point logic and precautionary zone.

### 600.5 – Technogenic Materials
Formalization of biosphere-foreign materials.

### 600.7 – SBE Detection Protocol
Four stage operational detection model.

### 600.8 – Mitigation and Containment
Operational response model.

### 600.9 – Monitoring and Verification
Three layer monitoring and verification framework.

---

## System Logic Chain

600.0 → 600.2 → 600.3 → 600.4 → 600.5 → 600.7 → 600.8 → 600.9 → 600.52

---

## Structural Outcome

The **600-series now forms a coherent vertical architecture**, from ontological definition to monitoring and mitigation.

The **600.1 Antiflux Parasite module remains unchanged**.

---

## Result

The **600-series now has a complete theoretical and operational foundation**.
